TITLE: 2005 jeep wrangler unlimited (tj/lj) loads of work done; cared for
ATTR: VIN: 1J4FA44S55P307179#condition: good#cylinders: 6 cylinders#drive: 4wd#fuel: gas#odometer: 137000#paint color: silver#title status: clean#transmission: automatic#type: offroad
MESSAGE: tl;dr#good jeep; well-loved on the trail and roads; and well-cared for in a shop. big ticket items done; professionally detailed; ready for you to enjoy.#yeah; this ad is crazy long. but im being thorough and honest to encourage serious buyers and hopefully avoid weird craigslist stories. lets have the rare; awesome craigslist story! read through and email me with any questions or when youd like to meet me for a test drive.#this ad has sections for#background#basics (the stuff in every ad)#transmission warranty info (a warranty!)#parts and repairs performed (loads of work done so you dont have to!)#upgrades (great ones)#honest downsides (only small ones!)#buying details (setting expectations so we dont hate this process)#background#its time to sell our well-loved jeep. weve taken great care of it since we bought it 2.5 years ago and had a great time with it; but life has other plans for us now. if youre looking for a wrangler that can be enjoyed around town; the deserts; or the mountains; this is a really great option. theres plenty you can do with it right now if you just want to explore (we have!); or you could turn this into a true monster of a rock crawler. this could be a great camping or overlanding rig too. if youre a jeep person; youre probably into this unlimited lj because of the 10 longer wheelbase and 5 extra overhang--way more space than the standard tj. (with the back bench out; you can fit something about 34 w between the wheel wells and 50 l from seats to rear door.) its a hard-to-find two-door trim that was only made from 2004-2006. the 4.0l 6 cylinder engine is a rock and can pull a trailer up to 3;500 pounds; making it great for work or play. its not a rubicon trim; but this fellow can hang in with a lot of beefy jeeps; while still being reasonably comfortable on the highway or around town.#basics#2005 jeep wrangler unlimited - tj/lj#4.0l i6 engine (a rockstar)#137;xxx miles#automatic transmission (42rle)#tires with lots of tread#soft top; hard doors; glass manual windows#aftermarket cd player with aux and usb inputs#aftermarket backup camera#passed smog in 3/2016#tags good until march 2018#towing capacity: 3;500 lbs#stock axles d33 front; d44 3.73 rear with trac-lok limited slip differential#oil just changed#professionally detailed inside and out on thursday 7/13#many upgrades; maintenance; and parts; so you should have a trouble-free experience. ill provide my repair log and receipts for the major work from my ownership.#transmission warranty until 4/2019 or another 80k miles#transmission info: http://www.jasperengines.com/jasper-reman-transmissions#warranty: http://qms.jasperengines.com/warranty.asp#we had a jasper transmission professionally installed in april 2016. it comes with a warranty for three years or 100;000 miles. that means parts and labor for any transmission problems are covered nationwide until april 2019 or 220;000 miles; whichever comes first. paperwork available for review when you come take a look; and will be provided if you buy it. i doubt youll find another wrangler like this with a transmission warranty.#parts and repairs#10/2014: all four lower control arms#10/2014: front calipers#10/2014: front sway bar links#10/2015: hinges on sunrider roof#10/2015: light stalk on steering wheel#1/2016: downstream o2 sensor#2/2016: status sensor on transfer case#4/2016: rebuilt transmission from jasper; under warranty! ($3000)#6/2017: rear main seal; oil pan and gasket (over $600 worth of repairs)#7/2017: full exhaust system replaced; all catalytic converters and o2 sensors ($1000 worth of maintenance)#upgrades#reese class iii tow hitch and 4-pin towing light connector#smittybilt steel glove box#side-mount jerry can holders (sorry; jerry cans not included)#all the rest professionally installed...#pro comp stage i 4 suspension lift#pro comp steering stabilizer#bf goodrich ko atii 33 tires; including the spare (about 17 months old w/ less than 20k miles)#smittybilt side armor rocker bars#rockhard front bumper with blue ox-compatible towing tabs (can be flat-towed behind rv). we actually used a readybrute tow bar and readybrake system that wed consider selling separately.#smittybilt winch (used it a couple times; its great!)#hood-mount trail jack#cb radio with magnetic front mount antenna#backup camera embedded in rear oem bumper#backup monitor embedded behind rearview mirror#hey; just bought new floor mats! sweet!#downsides; biggest to smallest#the top is solid and doesnt leak; but theres a less than quarter-inch whole above the back seat that we patched with a good patch kit (needle and thread plus adhesive). we havent had any problems; but i want to be upfront. the top is probably about 3.5-4 years old and the vinyl is fine; but another year or two id probably want to budget for a new one.#fenders are fading. theyre the original oem fenders. we sprayed them with bedliner last year and they looked good until this summer. starting to fade in spots again.#the carpet in the driver side footwell is ripped underneath the floor mats. but the floormats are brand-spanking new in the beginning of july! the rest of the interior is in acceptable condition. its no luxury car; but it looks okay.#theres just one dent rear left; one front right (previous owner) and some scratches here and there. the paint on side-view mirror mounts is also getting pretty worn. overall the outside is in fair shape for a wrangler of this age. pictures of any trouble spots are posted.#buying details#i think this is reasonably priced given the details above; the fact that it needs zero work; and the comparison to other wranglers on the market. if youre going to try to make an offer; please be realistic; serious; and ready to buy. i can be flexible on scheduling time for a test drive; though its easier for me to meet at the north end of balboa park/morley field as marked on the map. email me with any questions; or to suggest a time to come take a look.#in-person transactions only. no paypal; wires; or dealers please.

TITLE: 2006 wrangler unlimited rubicon
ATTR: condition: excellent#cylinders: 6 cylinders#drive: 4wd#fuel: gas#odometer: 87000#title status: clean#transmission: automatic
MESSAGE: up for sale is an incredibly rare vehicle. these longer wheelbase tjs; nicknamed the lj; where only produced by jeep from 2004-2006. they came with a 10 inch longer wheelbase; which offers a better drive on road and leaves more room in the rear for hauling equipment. this vehicle is even more rare; as it was one of the few produced in the rubicon configuration. this means that it came from the factory with dana 44 axles front and rear; as well as factory lockers. the unlimited rubicon also has double the towing capacity of the tj. this came from the factory as an offroad beast; and it has been further upgraded to make it perform even better.#this jeep has the following upgrades:#-4 inch long arm suspension kit#-2 inch body lift#-front and rear off-road bumpers#-rock rails#-9;000 lb winch - ive never been stuck in this jeep; but the winch has been super handy to get people out of the mud#-4 piaa offroad lights#-soft top#-tan seat covers front and rear#-full set of 33 bfg a/ts in good condition (im going to keep the coopers for another project)#this vehicle is in great shape. i bought it to get around on my ranch; but honestly its a pain in the ass to get in and out of it every time you have to open and close a gate. so; its been collecting dust in a barn for about a year now; so its time to go. this thing has not been offroaded; just driven around my ranch. its in absolutely amazing shape for a vehicle of its age and mileage. the body is completely rust free; and the underside is in as good a shape as the top. there are a few minor issues that need to be discussed. theres a crack in the windshield. theres a small dent/crack in the wheel on the spare tire. in my opinion its still fine to use as a spare if youre going to use the jeep locally. if i was going to drive it across the country id buy a new wheel. the previous owner cut out a circle below the gear shifter for some unknown reason. ive included pictures of the issues.#this thing is absolutely 100% ready to go. its upgraded with everything you could need; and its completely functional. just add fuel and go.#the jeep is located 2 hours east of dallas in the city of bogata. if youre interested; let me know and we can figure out a way to meet up.

ATTR: condition: excellent#cylinders: 6 cylinders#drive: 4wd#fuel: gas#odometer: 122923#paint color: white#title status: clean#transmission: manual
MESSAGE: 2000 jeep wrangler sahara#specs:#4.0l; 6-cylinder#4wd; 6-speed manual transmission#123;000 miles#5 new tires: 33 x 12.50 general grabber mud tires (4k miles on them)#4-inch rancho performance spring lift#smittybilt aftermarket front and rear bumpers#2 aftermarket lights wired to switch in dashboard#quadratec tan soft top with tinted rear windows#2 grab handles on roll bars#soundbar with light#ac/heat#background on jeep:#ive owned this jeep since december 2011 when it had about 110k miles. this is my third jeep. i purchased it from a middle-aged family friend in my neighborhood--it was his 12th jeep. he travelled to florida two years earlier and purchased from someone there. this guy knew his jeeps and took care of them. being my third jeep; i never took it off-roading (got that out of my system with my previous jeeps). it is garage kept and driven 3-4x a week within a 20 mile radius. when the previous owner bought it in florida; the jeep was factory/stock. he purchased the lift kit and aftermarket bumpers from 4-wheel parts on 1960 and had them install it. i replaced the top 2 years ago. the top has zero cracking; zippers work like new; and no tears of any kind where the top locks in above the side doors (jeep owners know this happens a lot to soft tops). i purchased 5 new general grabber mud tires about 2 years ago. the mileage on the jeep then was 118;000. so; these tires have 4k miles on them with a life expectancy of 50k miles. i replaced the clutch system about 4 months ago. i change the oil every 5k miles and use top quality oil. i also flush the radiator and replace fluids during every checkup. this jeep is in peak working condition. finally; i have all the receipts to show every tune-up; oil change; maintenance; etc. i am happy to scan and send to you if youd like to see what has been done to it over the past 3-4 years.#why im selling:#i would prefer to keep the jeep; but i am moving up north and jeeps just arent practical in the city. i am not trying to dump it off because of mechanical issues or any other shady reason. purely because of city traffic; cold weather; and high gas prices.#things to consider before you buy:#i want to be 100% transparent. i am happy to provide all receipts that show oil changes; maintenance; etc. you can even use these to track how many miles have been put on over the years. i will also provide you with my mechanics information (hes worked on it since 2012) if youd like to contact him about the jeep. similarly; you are welcome to take the jeep to your own mechanic to have him check it out. i encourage you to run a carfax report on the jeep (i will provide you with the vin upon request) so that you can double check its history. i have seen and test-driven a lot of jeeps--jeeps have a tendency for having hidden problems--so be a smart buyer and ill be a fair seller. finally; make sure that this is the type of vehicle you want! its rough; bouncy; eats gas (about 12-15 miles per gallon); and is not luxury...all the reasons why ive always loved jeeps. just make sure thats what you want too!#problems with jeep:#almost none. left headlight lamp is a little dingy and could be replaced. the stereo player doesnt recognize cds or aux chords--so stick to radio. i always flush the radiator when i take it in b/c the fluids get a little murky and i want to keep the engine as clean as possible.#respond via email or call/text me at (eight three two) - seven zero four - two nine three five

MESSAGE: i am looking to sell my 1998 jeep wrangler. i have driven this jeep for approximately 20;000 miles primarily used as a highway commuter. this jeep has no rust; has never been lifted; and has never experienced a death wobble. i did not have the time to take it up on many trails and i would like to buy something more efficient. the suspension is in great shape as it was not used for offroading; and it is a great starting point for someone looking to build a project. it is also a perfect fit for someone looking to have a reliable vehicle through the snow. this jeep has successfully taken me through more than a few crazy blizzards on i-25 where i was the only vehicle for miles that had not spun out and ended up in the ditch! i have followed a strict maintenance schedule; never going much further than 4;000 miles for each oil change. additionally; i regularly ran red line fuel system cleaner through it before each oil change. when i purchased this jeep the previous owner had pointed out that he had replaced the radiator and installed a glass pack muffler (which gives a great sound!). the previous owner included a new catalytic converter with the purchase of the jeep; and i had a shop install it at about 150;000 miles. other maintenance that has been performed on this jeep by me is as follows:#spark plugs @  155;000 miles#transmission oil flush and refill @  156;000 miles#4 new shocks @  158;000 miles#engine air filter @   150;000 & 160;000 miles#exhaust header @  161;000 miles (it was cracked when i bought it; the crack eventually spread which is why i replaced it)#(along with the header i replaced the gasket and header bolts)#(additionally; while replacing the exhaust header i had a chance to inspect all of the valves; which showed no signs of damage or unusual wear)#fan clutch @  161;000 miles (same time as the exhaust header)#serpentine belt @  161;000 miles (same time as the exhaust header)#front sway bar links @  161;500 miles#the ac has a small leak which has required me to charge it at least once each summer.#the soft top is bestop brand and can be easily dropped down in about 10 minutes. the only issue with the bestop is that the front windows are difficult to zip up after they have been opened. instead of zipping them down i recommend just popping the top half of each door off.#a new windshield is in order as you can see from the pictures; but it appears to be done cracking!#the only other issue that i have dealt with is 2nd gear becoming a little grumpy during the cold months. it needs to be handled gently (i kept it happy by double clutching into 2nd) when shifting into 2nd gear in the cold during the first 15 minutes or so of driving; but once the tranny gets warmed up its not much of a problem. i have not dealt with any grumpy gears during the warm months.#i have loved this jeep and watched over it with great care and it is a shame to say goodbye; but i need something better for gas mileage on the highway. feel free to text or email with any questions!#do not contact me with offers to help sell this jeep for me.#do not contact me if you are going to attempt to send me money over the internet.
